{"type":"message","id":"557cffb9","parentId":"27cb15c7","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:16:11.787Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Gateway status shows:\n- Service: Scheduled Task (missing) — the Windows scheduled task is missing\n- RPC probe: ok — the gateway is running\n- Listening: 127.0.0.1:18790 — gateway is listening\n\nSo the Gateway IS actually running (RPC probe ok, Listening), but the **Scheduled Task for the service is missing**. This means the cron jobs that rely on the Windows Scheduled Task won't run.\n\nHowever, if the Gateway itself is running (as a process), maybe the cron scheduling is handled by the gateway process itself, not the Windows Scheduled Task.\n\nLooking at the status more carefully:\n- \"Service: Scheduled Task (missing)\" — this is about the Windows service/task that auto-starts the gateway. The gateway itself is running (RPC probe ok).\n\n\n- The cron runs shown in `openclaw status` are tracked by the gateway, so they're being recorded, but the scheduled task itself isn't installed in Windows. I should restart the gateway to see if that gets the cron jobs running again, though the real issue might be that the gateway process is up but the Windows scheduled task isn't, which means auto-restart on reboot won't work.\n\nLet me check the recent logs to see what's actually happening with the cron execution."},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway 本身在跑（RPC probe ok），但 **Windows Scheduled Task 丢失**了，这可能导致 cron 没法自动触发。让我看看今天的日志：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ap5ru6g0pcxz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\linkang\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\openclaw\\openclaw-2026-04-04.log\" -Tail 50 2>&1 | Select-String -Pattern \"cron|aa7a03fc|ed08c32f|f988438d|error|Error\" | Select-Object -Last 30","yieldMs":10000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"out