{"type":"message","id":"7f133065","parentId":"b16ec76b","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:16:28.335Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the logs, I see some key issues:\n\n1. `missing scope: operator.read` - when the CLI tries to connect to gateway, it lacks proper permissions/scopes\n2. `gateway closed (1000)` - the gateway is closing connections\n\nThe `gateway closed (1000)` errors happen when the CLI tries to run commands. This seems like the gateway is not accepting connections from the CLI properly.\n\nBut importantly - the cron jobs DID run (lastRunAtMs shows 29 hours ago), so the cron scheduler is active. The problem is the DELIVERY step is failing.\n\nWait, the logs I looked at are from when I was running CLI commands just now. Let me look at earlier in the log file to see what happened around 11:30 today.\n\n\nActually, looking at the openclaw status output again - the \"Gateway service: Scheduled Task installed · missing\" is a Windows Scheduled Task issue. The OpenClaw cron jobs are triggered by a Windows Scheduled Task (not by the gateway itself). The Windows Scheduled Task is \"missing\", which explains why cron hasn't fired today (Saturday 11:30). The cron expressions are correct, but if the Windows Scheduled Task that fires the cron scheduler is missing, jobs won't trigger. I need to fix this."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 问题找到了：**Windows Scheduled Task 丢失**了。OpenClaw 的 cron 调度依赖 Windows Scheduled Task 来触发，今天的11:30没有按时触发就是因为这个。\n\n需要重新安装 Scheduled Task，我来执行：\n\n[[reply_to_current]] 找到了两个问题：\n\n**1. Windows Scheduled Task 丢失了** — cron 11:30 没有触发就是因为这个\n**2. Delivery target 还有残留的 `user:` 前缀**（旅游攻略那个还没改干净）\n\n我来一起修复：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9glsxezbbcdb_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\linkang\\.openclaw\\cron\\jobs.json","old_string":"        \"target\": \"user:ou_e48f6c4c0395f45b74b51525f348678b\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 17