{"type":"message","id":"fa87c599","parentId":"d3eaee07","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:17:43.858Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`schtasks create failed: 拒绝访问` - Access denied. This means the current user doesn't have permission to create a Scheduled Task. This might require running as Administrator.\n\nThis is a Windows permission issue. The user would need to run OpenClaw as administrator to install the Scheduled Task.\n\nHowever, there's another approach - I can try to run the cron jobs manually right now to test if the delivery works. Since the user asked \"你看看呢\" - they want to know the current status.\n\nActually, let me think about what the user is asking. They said \"你看看呢\" which means \"can you check on it?\" - they want to know why the push didn't work today.\n\nSo the issue is:\n\n\nThe Scheduled Task that triggers cron jobs is missing due to access denied when trying to reinstall it. The jobs are configured correctly with the daily schedule, but they never actually ran because nothing triggered them this morning. Delivery failures from earlier attempts might have been due to the `user:` prefix issue, but the real problem is that the cron jobs need administrative privileges to set up the Scheduled Task properly."},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 好，情况搞清楚了：\n\n**两个独立的问题：**\n\n**1. Cron 根本没触发** — Scheduled Task 安装失败（权限问题，需要管理员权限），今天的 11:30 实际上没有任何任务被触发\n\n**2. Delivery target 残留问题** — 之前有两个任务的 target 带 `user:` 前缀，现在已全部修正\n\n**Schedule Task 修复不了**（`schtasks create failed: 拒绝访问`），需要用管理员权限打开命令提示符或 PowerShell，然后运行：\n```\nopenclaw gateway install\n```\n\n在那之前，**要不要我手动跑一次推送任务**，测试一下 delivery target 改好之后能不能正常推送到飞书？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775290650799}}
